When using an malformed image ID format with euca-deregister, error message returned is malformed.  This doesn't follow error code and behavior exhibited by ec2-register (breaks AWS compatibility).

*[euca-deregister]*

{code}
# euca-deregister emi-5C
DeregisterImageType: Get unique failed for ImageInfo using example: [ImageInfo imageName=null description=null architecture=null imagePublic=null platform=null imageType=null permissions=[] productCodes=[] deviceMappings=[] imageSizeBytes=null fullName=null ownerUserId=null ownerUserName=null ownerAccountNumber=null ownerAccountName=null uniqueName=null ownerFullNameCached=null state=null lastState=null stateChangeStack=null displayName=emi-5C id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]
{code}

*[ec2-deregister]*

{code}
$ ec2-deregister ami-2e4
Client.InvalidAMIID.Malformed: Invalid id: "ami-2e4"
{code}

*[References]*

* http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/APIReference/api-error-codes.html (refer to InvalidAMIID.Malformed; maybe want to change it to InvalidEMIID.Malformed)
